summary: So far this has been an unpopular opinion, but would you agree that Captain America and Luther Hargreeves have similar energies?...
question: So far this has been an unpopular opinion, but would you agree that Captain America and Luther Hargreeves have similar energies? And that Five = Tony Stark?
answer:
People like Captain America because he’s the same without his powers. He’s brave and selfless and he’s like that just because that’s his personality.

Luther isn’t naturally “Captain America.” Luther is what happens when someone tries to “make” a “Captain America” out of a regular person. He’s fake captain America. He acts like a leader because he’s told to, not because it comes naturally.

When push comes to shove cap does the right thing every time. Luther doesn’t. In fact, when push comes to shove, Luther gets drunk at a rave and locks his sister up.

Five as Ironman I can see cuz they’ve both very aware they’re smarter than everyone else in the room. However difference is deep down Five 100% believes he’s better than his siblings. Tony Stark however I would say is all insecurity underneath the egotistic exterior.

summary: Once an Avenger, Always an Avenger!
title: Once an Avenger, Always an Avenger!
body:
Iron Man #178

Amusing story about some children who dress and act like the Avengers.

  • It’s another silly script from Assistant Editors’ Month. But it’s far from being the worst. It’s actually funny in places. Such as when Young Iron Man turns to coke in his darkest hour.
  • Luke McDonnell (18 of 37). 

6/10
